<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-355-658  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 355 658.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  April 1990 v27 n4 p38(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Shorten the road to recovery: scheme features computerizedblueprint as key to fast on-site restoration. (combinedcomputer-aided design and database system track communicationsystem configuration)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bloom, Greg.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Comprehensive documentation systems combining computer-aideddesign and database capabilities provide a continuous record ofthe state of a telecommunications system, facilitating bothday-to-day management and disaster recovery.andP;  Rapid restoration ofa communications system to its original state before a disruptionis important to a company's operations and to minimizing the costof using a backup service.andP;  Such services may require a $1,000 to$30,000 monthly contract plus up to $100,000 or more for actualuse of the services' backup facilities during an emergency.andP;  Fulland continuously up-to-date documentation of a telecommunicationsnetwork's physical hardware and logical attributes will minimizeboth the time and costs involved in using a backup service byspeeding restoration to the pre-disruption configuration.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DocumentationComputer SystemsNetworksCommunications CircuitsBack-Up SystemsComputer-Aided DesignIntegrated Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>